A few things:

1. Rename c:&#92;junit3.8.1&#92;junit3.8.1 to just c:&#92;junit3.8.1. That&#39;s just
confusing.
2. junit.jar must be on the CLASSPATH and fully-qualified, which you
have.
3. The tests are in the package junit.tests, so the folder CONTAINING
the tree junit/tests/* must be on the CLASSPATH. In my case, it&#39;s
d:&#92;junit3.8.1.
4. Don&#39;t set your CLASSPATH using environment variables. Write a shell
script and launch it when you launch your Command Prompt. The cleaner
your environment, the better. :)

Good luck.

